Uses of Package
socialSecurityDeathIndex

  • Classes in socialSecurityDeathIndex used by socialSecurityDeathIndex 
    Class and Description
    DatabaseConnection
    A default implementation of the IDatabaseConnection interface.
    Subclasses inherit from DatabaseConnection to establish a connection to a database from a specific vendor (sponsor).
    These subclasses must implement at least the ConnectToDatabase method.
    DbConnectionException
    Exception thrown on failure of an attempt to create or connect an IDatabaseConnection
    DuplicateKeyException
    Exception thrown on an attempt to add a record, with a unique key (the Social Security Account Number) equal to the key of an existing record, to a Social Security Death Index database
    IDatabaseConnection
    Database-agnostic interface implemented by any class representing a connection to a database hosting Social Security Death Index data
    IDeathRecord
    Interface implemented by any class representing Social Security Death Index master file records.
    MainForm
    Simple user interface form to enable loading and querying Social Security Death Index databases.
    This form contains the main() method for the SSDI application.
    SSDIprogram
    Simple client program for loading the master files and executing queries
    TimeSpan
    A time interval, specified via starting and ending Date date/timestamps.
    The TimeSpan class enables the specification of birth/death dates that are uncertain in day-of-month (or similar uncertainties).
